📢 **Exciting News from UTSG Debate Club!**

We’re thrilled to announce our first in-person round table debate event of the year! 🗣️✨

📅 Date: September 26
⏰ Time:4:00 PM - 6:00 PM
📍 Location:OISE, Room 5250 (252 Bloor Street West, Toronto, ON M5S 1V6) 

This is a fantastic opportunity to engage in stimulating discussions on a range of economic, political, and social issues in a welcoming, informal setting. Whether you’re a seasoned debater or a complete beginner, we encourage you to join us for an evening of insightful conversations.

Don’t forget to RSVP through the link in our bio and feel free to reach out if you have any questions. Looking forward to seeing you there!

#Debate #UTSG #Networking #PublicSpeaking #CriticalThinking #StudentLife #UToronto

Come join UTSPAN at our first SPL x UTSPAN Data Chellenge Seminar on Wednesday, Sept 18th at 7pm! 
Hear from MLSE Biometrics Specialist Rob Mackowiak on how he has used SPL's open data to perform biomechanical research on movement variability! You won't want to miss this great chance to get inspired by his work for your projects!

Join us on Zoom this Tuesday at 7 PM for our first UTSPAN Hour of the year led by our exec Zeke! These are interactive educational tutorials, usually geared toward beginners in data science. 
Find the link to the Zoom in our Discord linked in our bio!

We're excited that the SPLxUTSPAN Data Challenge is about to begin! An amazing 249 students from various schools and disciplines have expressed interest so far, and we can't wait to kick things off this Tuesday, September 10th, from 7-8 p.m. in BA1160 (40 St. George St.). The event will feature introductions from UTSPAN, MLSE, and TISS, followed by a data visualization demo led by Rob Mackowiak (MLSE biomechanics specialist), and will conclude with a Q&A session. If you can't attend in-person, you can join virtually via Zoom by filling out the interest form in our linktree in bio.

Also, don't forget to join the discord from our linktree too!

We look forward to seeing everyone either in-person or virtually on Tuesday night!

UofT Sailing t-shirts available to order ⭐️ 🌊 The funds go to support the sailing program and varsity team at UofT while brining excitement for the sport ⛵️

Each shirt is $25 and can be ordered from the link in bio.
